\c 23
\s1 Rules about just behaviour
\p
\v 1 “Don’t spread false news. Don’t help guilty people by giving false testimony in court.
\p
\v 2 “Don’t join in the majority in doing evil. Don’t side with them ny giving false witness in court to distort/reverse the truth.
\v 3 Also don’t side with someone in a court case just because he is poor.
\p
\v 4 “If you see your enemies’ ox or donkey lost, return it to them.
\v 5 If you see someone who hates you, and his donkey falls because of the weight on it is too heavy, help him so that his donkey can get back up. Don’t leave that person in a difficult situation.
\p
\v 6 “Don’t distort/reverse the truth in a case to take away someone’s rights because he is poor.
\p
\v 7 “Don’t make false accusations and don’t sentence an innocent person to death. I will not let go of anyone who does that.
\p
\v 8 “Don’t accept bribe because bribe makes a person blind and
